fields.description:
When esi-install-image is run but same version of the image has already been installed (via calyptos/eucalyptus-cookbook or manually), the manifest is modified for the image and it cannot start the instance with the error:

{code:java}
[root@g-05-03 ~]# esi-install-image --install-default --region localhost
Installing Service Image...
Found tarball /usr/share/eucalyptus/service-images/eucalyptus-service-image-1.49.tar.xz
Decompressing tarball: /usr/share/eucalyptus/service-images/eucalyptus-service-image-1.49.tar.xz
Installing image from eucalyptus-service-image.raw
Bundling, uploading and registering image to bucket: eucalyptus-service-image-1.49
Error: Unable to install imaging worker due to:
euca-install-image: error (InvalidAMIName.Duplicate): AMI name eucalyptus-service-image-v1.49 is already in use by EMI emi-1332d615
{code}

fields.summary: Instance manifest was changed after registration

comments.body: The suggestion is to check if the image already exists.

Until this fix goes live this is the work-around I have given to customers:

# eval `clcadmin-assume-system-credentials`
# esi-describe-images (Note the name of the default image used for each instance type)
# euca-deregister <image-name>
# esi-install-image --install-default --region localhost (This command should complete without any error messages)
# esi-describe-images (Note the new name of the default service image)
